Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbols. Clay fine buff-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: A common stamp. Petrie draw one similar piece from Naukratis (EES XVII p. 31, 3). Name Imas.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0929)
